sentences: J’Kerian Morgan (born March 22, 1989), known professionally as Lotic, is an American electronic musician based in Berlin.
She was invited by Björk to produce two official Vulnicura remixes in 2016.
Her full-length debut, Power, was released in 2018.
Morgan first became interested in DJing in 2009 after seeing a Kingdom set while still a student at UT Austin.
After graduating college in 2012, Morgan moved to Berlin with her boyfriend to pursue a career in music while working for Ableton.
The next year, she released the mixtape Fallout, which she followed with the Damsel in Distress mixtape in 2014.
Morgan released two EPs in 2015: Heterocetera and Agitations.
In 2016, she was commissioned by Björk to produce two official remixes of "Notget" from Vulnicura; she also served as an opening act on the Berlin date of the Vulnicura Tour.
That fall, she scored a promotional video for fashion brand ifeoma’s spring/summer 2017 collection.
Her full-length debut, Power, was released in 2018.
Along with Floating Points and Raven, Morgan scored the 2019 KDV Dance Ensemble performance piece "Las Casas Invisibles" choreographed by Kianí del Valle.
She also contributed to a remix compilation of tracks from Polish cellist Resina's 2018 album Traces.
In May 2020, Morgan announced a deal with Houndstooth Records after Tri Angle records shut down the previous month.
Lotic released the single “Come Unto Me” on August 17, 2021.
The second single from Water, "Emergency", was released on September 21, 2021.
Pitchfork locates Lotic within the broader trend of "conceptronica" that arose in the 2010s, comparing her to artists like Elysia Crampton and Chino Amobi.
2018's Power marked a stylistic shift for Lotic.
Morgan is transgender, first announcing her transition in 2018.
In 2016, Morgan was evicted from her apartment after the individual she subleased from did not pay the full rent.
She also soundtracked the autumn/winter 2017 Julius Society show at Paris Fashion Week.
Lotic rose to prominence through her involvement with the Janus Collective in the early 2010s as well as with a string of EPs released during this time.

Later that year, she became affiliated with the Janus Collective, a group described in the New York Times  as part of an enclave of American expatriates “ taking over sleepy venues, creating their own parties and leaving a significant imprint on the city’s musical program.”
The next year, she released the mixtape Fallout, which she followed with the Damsel in Distress mixtape in 2014.
That fall, she scored a promotional video for fashion brand ifeoma’s spring/summer 2017 collection.
That year, she also performed in and scored "Embryogenesis" and "Fleshless Beast", dance pieces choreographed by Roderick George.
In May 2020, Morgan announced a deal with Houndstooth Records after Tri Angle records shut down the previous month.
The following single, "Cocky", was released that August.
That same day, she announced that her second studio album, Water, was to be released on October 29 of that year.

Although she now lives in Berlin, her work draws from the African American experience; her sound pays homage to ball culture and drumlines and the album Power was inspired in part by Between the World and Me by Ta-Nehisi Coates.
